knowledge-path-hunt-s1-name = Principle of Strife
knowledge-path-hunt-s1-desc =
    Opens up the Path of Hunt to you.
    Allows you to transmute a pistol and a knife into a Serpentine Revolver. Makeshift Pistols and Flare Guns will both suffice.
    ---
    "One's name means nothing in war. There are only titles: Victor and Defeated."

knowledge-path-hunt-s2-name = Hunter's Grasp
knowledge-path-hunt-s2-desc =
     Your Mansus Grasp gains the ability to refill an empty bullet casing.
    ---
    "When one is prey, they must be resourceful. The Fugitive knew this well."

knowledge-path-hunt-s3-name = Watchtower Striving
knowledge-path-hunt-s3-desc =
    Grants you the Watchtower Striving spell, which places a tower that redirects bullets towards heathens when hit.
    This spell requires a Focus to cast.
    ---
    "The Warden kept a vigilant watch from on high. It refused to become Defeated."

knowledge-path-hunt-s4-name = Mark of Hunt
knowledge-path-hunt-s4-desc =
    Your Mansus Grasp will cause your prey to be slowed for a short time.
    ---
    "The Fugitive was clever. It had done this before. It had been Warden before, and it would be again."

knowledge-path-hunt-s5-name = Meteoric Pouch
knowledge-path-hunt-s5-desc =
    Allows you to transmute a pill canister and a pipe into a Meteoric Pouch, which works as a portable ammo fabricator.
    It produces Meteoric Bullets, which phase through walls.
    ---
    "No wall could hold the Fugitive. The Warden knew this. It had been Fugitive before, and it would be again."

knowledge-path-hunt-s6-name = Serpent's Focus
knowledge-path-hunt-s6-desc =
    Grants you the Serpent's Focus ability, which allows you to see living things through walls, but blacks out your vision.
    This spell requires a Focus to cast.
    ---
    "As all twins, they are crafty. As all twins, they squabble. As all twins, they have a sense for one another."

knowledge-path-hunt-s7-name = Lion's Bane
knowledge-path-hunt-s7-desc =
    Allows you to transmute a pistol, some meat, and a pair of eyes into a Lionhunter's Rifle.
    It comes full of .60 meteoric bullets, and has long-range sniper sights.
    ---
    "They are one and the same, these twins. Their names are not names. They are titles. Winner and Loser."

knowledge-path-hunt-s8-name = Warden's Shroud
knowledge-path-hunt-s8-desc =
    Allows you to transmute a scarf, a glass shard, and a brain into a Skaptodon Cloak, which allows the wearer to become invisible while still.
    ---
    "The Warden was on the backfoot. It refused to become a Fugitive, and so it hid. But a Warden does not hide."

knowledge-path-hunt-s9-name = Manhunt's Reversal
knowledge-path-hunt-s9-desc =
    The Ascension ritual of the Path of Hunt.
    Bring 3 handcuffed corpses to a Transmutation Rune to complete the ritual.
    This ritual will complete your transformation from Prey to Hunter.
    You will redirect all projectiles that hit you back at your foes.
    However, you can still be hurt by melee weapons and lasers.
